description: After the ultimate fish taco recipe? Try this spiced barramundi that's baked, topped with a zingy mayo dressing and wrapped up in lettuce leaves.
keywords: Taco,Pescatarian,Low saturated fat,Summer,Barramundi,Fish,High protein,High fibre,Wheat free,Quick & easy lunch,Autumn,Apr 2021
name: Cajun Fish & Lettuce Tacos Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 0.5 small lime, juiced (plus extra lime wedges to serve)
1 tbs coriander leaves, finely chopped (plus extra sprigs to serve)

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Line a baking tray with baking paper.
Combine oil and 1 tbs seasoning in a large bowl. Add fish and rub to coat. Place on tray and bake for 10 minutes or until cooked through.

Meanwhile, place mayonnaise, lime juice and remaining seasoning in a small bowl. Stir until combined. Mix cabbage, onion and chopped coriander in a separate bowl. Drizzle with half the mayonnaise dressing.
Fill lettuce leaves with flaked fish, cabbage mixture, mayonnaise dressing and extra coriander. Serve with extra lime wedges.
